  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: March 17, 2026</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The Wyoming Youth Resource Map mobile application ("App") is developed and maintained by Casper Youth Hub. This policy describes how we handle information when you use the App.</p>

    <h2>Data We Access and Collect</h2>
    <p>We disclose below all types of data the App may access or collect. Our practices are minimal and privacy-focused.</p>

    <h3>Location Data (Optional)</h3>
    <p>When you tap "Near Me," the App may request permission to access your device's approximate location. <strong>Usage:</strong> This data is used only to sort resource listings by proximity on your device. It is <strong>never</strong> transmitted to our servers or any third party. Location access is entirely optional — the App functions fully without it. You may deny or revoke location permission at any time.</p>

    <h3>Saved Resources (Local Only)</h3>
    <p>Resources you save as favorites are stored locally on your device using on-device storage. <strong>Usage:</strong> This data is used only to display your saved list within the App. It is never transmitted to our servers or any third party.</p>

    <h3>Cached Data</h3>
    <p>The App temporarily caches resource listings on your device to improve performance. <strong>Usage:</strong> This cache contains only publicly available resource information (names, addresses, phone numbers, descriptions) and is automatically refreshed. It is not transmitted to our servers beyond the initial API request to fetch listings.</p>

    <h2>Health Data</h2>
    <p>The App displays a directory of youth-serving resources, including mental health, counseling, crisis services, substance use support, and other health-related programs. <strong>We do not collect, store, or transmit any health data from you.</strong> We do not ask for or access your health conditions, medical history, mental health status, or any other health information. The resource listings shown in the App are publicly available directory information — we do not infer or collect health-related data about you based on your use of the App.</p>

    <h2>Data We Do NOT Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect personal information (name, email, phone number)</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect, access, or transmit any health data (health conditions, medical history, mental health status, or similar)</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use analytics, tracking, or advertising SDKs</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> create user accounts</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> share any data with third parties</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use cookies</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>The App connects to the Wyoming Youth Resource Map API (casperyouthhubmap.org) to fetch publicly available resource listings. No personal data is sent in these requests.</p>
    <p>When you tap external links (directions, phone numbers, websites, Google Forms), you are directed to third-party services (Apple Maps, Google Maps, phone dialer, web browser) which have their own privacy policies.</p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is designed to help young people ages 11–20 find resources. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children or any other users.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>All data stored by the App (saved resources, cached listings) resides only on your device. Uninstalling the App removes all stored data.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:</p>
